{{Infobox project | name = Akon Lighting Africa | logo = Akon Lighting Africa.png | image = | caption = | mission_statement = Providing Africans with access to electricity | type = Non Commercial | products = | location = [[Africa]] | owner = [[Akon]] | founder = [[Akon]], [[Samba Bathily]], Thione Niang | key_people = | established = February 2014 | disestablished = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | funding = China Jiangsu International Economic And Technical Cooperation Group <ref name="atlanta"/> | current_status = Active | website = [http://akonlightingafrica.com/ AkonLightingAfrica.com] }}
'''Akon Lighting Africa''' is a project started in 2014 by former music artist [[Akon]] with [[Samba Bathily]] and Thione Niang which aims to provide [[electricity]] by [[solar energy]] in [[Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Insight |first1=News |title=Akon unveils new solar campaign for Africa |url=http://www.insightnews.com/news/13643-akon-unveils-new-solar-campaign-for-africa |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705062734/http://www.insightnews.com/news/13643-akon-unveils-new-solar-campaign-for-africa |archivedate=2015-07-05 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Akon lights Africa for better future|url=http://www.enca.com/world/akon-lights-africa-better-future|website=enca}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Musician Akon works to light up Africa|url=http://edition.cnn.com/videos/world/2015/06/08/segment-walker-vause-akon-electricity-africa.cnn|website=CNN}}</ref> Their initial technique is to install [[Solar street light]]s and small energy systems.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.devex.com/news/inside-akon-lighting-africa-87342|title=Inside Akon Lighting Africa|date=2015-11-25|newspaper=Devex|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-04}}</ref>
== History == According to [[Akon]], he and Thione Niang grew up in [[Kaolack Region]], [[Senegal]] in a town without electricity. In 2013 both decided to help drive Africa’s transformation. [[Samba Bathily]] joined them and provided targeted solutions through his company, Solektra INT, which supplies solar-powered equipment. By combining their networks, they launched the project in February 2014. The projects now provides electricity in 14 [[Africa]]n countries and employs over 5,000<ref name="atlanta">{{Cite news|url=http://www.globalatlanta.com/singer-akons-unconventional-keys-to-social-investing-in-africa/|title=Singer Akon's Unconventional Keys to Social Investing in Africa - Global Atlanta|date=2015-06-01|newspaper=Global Atlanta|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> mainly young people who install and maintain solar equipment.<ref>{{cite web|title=Three men backing one mission: widening the access to electricity|url=http://akonlightingafrica.com/our-activities/origins/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Akon talks to Folly Bah Thibault|url=http://america.aljazeera.com/watch/shows/talk-to-al-jazeera/articles/2015/2/5/akon-talks-to-folly.html|website=Al Jazeera America}}</ref>
== Countries == Since launching in 2014, Akon's group has operations in 14 nations, including [[Guinea]], [[Senegal]], [[Mali]], [[Niger]], [[Benin]] and [[Sierra Leone]].{{fact|date=June 2018}}
== Solar Academy ==
The group announced the launch of the solar academy in [[Bamako, Mali]] at the second [[United Nations]] Sustainable Energy for All Forum, in [[New York City]]. Solar Academy will teach students about using solar panels by which they can light [[Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Akon to light up Africa |url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/world/artikel.php?ID=361759 |website=GhanaWeb |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612180700/http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/world/artikel.php?ID=361759 |archivedate=2015-06-12 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Akon Lighting Africa Moves Towards Bringing Electricity To 600M People|url=http://afkinsider.com/97777/akon-lighting-africa-moves-towards-bringing-electricity-to-600m-people/|website=AFK Insider}}</ref> Samba Bathily told in an interview: "We have the sun and innovative technologies to bring electricity to homes and communities. We now need to consolidate African expertise and that is our objective.".<ref>{{cite web|title=Akon creates institution to educate solar engineers in Africa|url=http://www.mnn.com/earth-matters/energy/blogs/akon-creates-institution-to-educate-solar-engineers-in-africa|website=mnn}}</ref>
