In [[Etruscan mythology]], '''Selvans''' was god of the woodlands, cognate with [[Roman mythology|Roman]] [[Silvanus (mythology)|Silvanus]]. His name is 10th on the list of 16&nbsp;gods on the outer rim of the [[Piacenza Liver]] (a [[bronze]] model of a [[sheep]]’s [[liver]] used as a reference or teaching tool for [[divination]]).

